title: Woman ran before Melbourne fatal accident - 9news.com.au
text:
Woman ran before Melbourne fatal accident By AAP 
A woman who was killed by a speeding car in Melbourne's city centre tried to run for her life when she realised the car was coming towards her. 
NSW woman Tanami Nayler, 24, was killed instantly when a car driven by New Zealander Nicholas Michael Davison ran a red light and struck her as she crossed a road on July 30 last year. 
Davison, 23, pleaded guilty in the Victorian County Court on Wednesday to five charges, including culpable driving causing death, reckless conduct endangering life, and failing to stop after a fatal accident. Â© AAP 2017
